data.name: InvalidKeyIdentifier
data.value: The provided number must be a valid key identifier.
data.comment: Thrown when an invalid key identifier is passed to the GetKeyBinding or SetKeyBinding methods.

data.name: WrongKeyBindingCount
data.value: The provided collection of bindings must contain exactly {0} elements.
data.comment: Thrown when the KeyLayout constructor is passed an invalid number of KeyBinding elements.

data.name: PointComponentsMustBeLargerThanMinValue
data.value: The components of the provided point must be larger than Int16.MinValue.
data.comment: Thrown when the components of a PointS are equal to Int16.MinValue and you attempt to negate them.

data.name: BadArraySegmentEndpoints
data.value: The array segment [{0},{1}] does not fit into the array's bounds.
data.comment: Thrown when an array segment defined by endpoints does not fit into the array's bounds.

data.name: BadArraySegmentLength
data.value: The array segment starting at {0} with length {1} does not fit into the array's bounds.
data.comment: Thrown when an array segment defined by offset and length does not fit into the array's bounds.

data.name: CapacityMustBePositive
data.value: The provided capacity must be a positive integer.
data.comment: Thrown when the value of a capacity argument is a non-positive integer.

data.name: CapacityMustBeNonNegative
data.value: The provided capacity must be a non-negative integer.
data.comment: Thrown when the value of a capacity argument is a negative integer.

data.name: CountMustBePositive
data.value: The provided count must be a positive integer.
data.comment: Thrown when the value of a count argument is a non-positive integer.

data.name: OffsetMustBeNonNegative
data.value: The provided offset must be a non-negative integer.
data.comment: Thrown when the value of an offset argument is a negative integer.

data.name: CountMustBeNonNegative
data.value: The provided count argument must be a non-negative integer.
data.comment: Thrown when the value of a count argument is a negative integer.

data.name: PaddingLengthMustBePositive
data.value: The provided padding length must be a positive integer.
data.comment: Thrown when the value of the padding length argument is a non-positive integer.

data.name: StringMustBeShorterThanPaddingLength
data.value: The provided string must be shorter than the provided padding length.
data.comment: Thrown when the provided string is not shorter than the provided padding length.

data.name: LengthMustBeNonNegative
data.value: The provided length must be a non-negative integer.
data.comment: Thrown when the value of a length argument is a negative integer.

data.name: OffsetMustBeAheadOfCurrentPosition
data.value: The provided offset must be ahead of the current position.
data.comment: Thrown when the value of an offset argument is not ahead of the current stream position.

data.name: EndOfStreamReached
data.value: The end of the stream was reached.
data.comment: Thrown when the end of a stream was reached during a reading operation.

data.name: StringLengthMustBeEven
data.value: The length of the provided string must be an even number.
data.comment: Thrown when the length of a string argument is not an even number.

data.name: StringMustContainOnlyHexDigits
data.value: The provided string must consist only of hexadecimal digits.
data.comment: Thrown when a string argument contains characters that are not hexadecimal digits.

data.name: AesKeyMustBe32Bytes
data.value: The provided key array consist of exactly 32 bytes.
data.comment: Thrown when the an AES key array is not 32 bytes long.

data.name: ShuffleTableMustBe256Bytes
data.value: The provided table must consist of exactly 256 bytes.
data.comment: Thrown when a shuffle table argument is not exactly 256 bytes long.

data.name: IvMustBe4Bytes
data.value: The provided IV must be exactly 4 bytes long.
data.comment: Thrown when a provided IV array is not exactly 4 bytes long.

data.name: SegmentTooShort
data.value: The segment must have at least {0} elements.
data.comment: Thrown when a segment does not have enough elements.

data.name: PacketLengthMustBeMoreThan2Bytes
data.value: The packet length must be a number larger than 2.
data.comment: Thrown when a packet length less than 2 when constructing a header for the packet.

data.name: ReceiveEventHasNoSubscribers
data.value: The receive event has no subscribers.

data.value: The event cannot have more than one subscriber.
